// The magic: use Animal reference, store Dog/Cat objects
Animal a1 = new Dog("Bruno", "Lab");
Animal a2 = new Cat("Kitty");

a1.makeSound();  // Bruno says: Woof!  (Dog's version)
a2.makeSound();  // Kitty says: Meow! (Cat's version)
Why this is powerful
