ūüíĘMultithreading
A thread is a separate path of execution. Multithreading lets your program do multiple things at the same time.

ūüíĘThe Thread class
class MyTask extends Thread {
    private String taskName;

    public MyTask(String name) { taskName = name; }

    @Override
    public void run() {  // code that runs in its own thread
        for (int i = 1; i <= 3; i++) {
            System.out.println(taskName + ": step " + i);
        }
    }
}

MyTask t1 = new MyTask("Download");
MyTask t2 = new MyTask("Upload");
t1.start();  // starts new thread ‚ÄĒ don't call run() directly
t2.start();  // runs concurrently with t1
