ūüíĘExecutorService ‚ÄĒ the modern way
import java.util.concurrent.*;

ExecutorService pool = Executors.newFixedThreadPool(4); // 4 threads

pool.submit(() -> System.out.println("Task 1"));
pool.submit(() -> System.out.println("Task 2"));
pool.submit(() -> System.out.println("Task 3"));

pool.shutdown(); // wait for all tasks to finish
ūüíĘsynchronized ‚ÄĒ preventing data corruption
class Counter {
    private int count = 0;

    public synchronized void increment() {
        count++;  // only one thread at a time can run this
    }

    public int getCount() { return count; }
}
